"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#bewit-limitations\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Bewit Limitations\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"Special care must be taken when issuing bewit credentials to third parties. Bewit credentials are valid until expiration and cannot\\nbe revoked or limited without using other means. Whatever resource they grant access to will be completely exposed to anyone with\\naccess to the bewit credentials which act as bearer credentials for that particular resource. While bewit usage is limited to GET\\nrequests only and therefore cannot be used to perform transactions or change server state, it can still be used to expose private\\nand sensitive information.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"host-header-forgery\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#host-header-forgery\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Host Header Forgery\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"Hawk validates the incoming request MAC against the incoming HTTP Host header. However, unless the optional \"),a(\"code\",[t._v(\"host\")]),t._v(\" and \"),a(\"code\",[t._v(\"port\")]),t._v(\"\\noptions are used with \"),a(\"code\",[t._v(\"server.authenticate()\")]),t._v(\", a malicious client can mint new host names pointing to the server's IP address and\\nuse that to craft an attack by sending a valid request that's meant for another hostname than the one used by the server. Server\\nimplementors must manually verify that the host header received matches their expectation (or use the options mentioned above).\")]),a(\"h1\",{attrs:{id:\"frequently-asked-questions\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#frequently-asked-questions\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Frequently Asked Questions\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"where-is-the-protocol-specification\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#where-is-the-protocol-specification\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Where is the protocol specification?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"If you are looking for some prose explaining how all this works, \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"this is it\")]),t._v(\". \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" is being developed as an open source\\nproject instead of a standard. In other words, the \"),a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"/hueniverse/hawk/tree/master/lib\"}},[t._v(\"code\")]),t._v(\" is the specification. Not sure about\\nsomething? Open an issue!\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"is-it-done\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#is-it-done\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Is it done?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"As of version 0.10.0, \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" is feature-complete. However, until this module reaches version 1.0.0 it is considered experimental\\nand is likely to change. This also means your feedback and contribution are very welcome. Feel free to open issues with questions\\nand suggestions.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"where-can-i-find-hawk-implementations-in-other-languages\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#where-can-i-find-hawk-implementations-in-other-languages\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Where can I find \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" implementations in other languages?\")]),a(\"p\",[a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\"'s only reference implementation is provided in JavaScript as a node.js module. However, it has been ported to other languages.\\nThe full list is maintained \"),a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/hueniverse/hawk/issues?labels=port&state=closed\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\"}},[t._v(\"here\")]),t._v(\". Please add an issue if you are\\nworking on another port. A cross-platform test-suite is in the works.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"why-isn-t-the-algorithm-part-of-the-challenge-or-dynamically-negotiated\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#why-isn-t-the-algorithm-part-of-the-challenge-or-dynamically-negotiated\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Why isn't the algorithm part of the challenge or dynamically negotiated?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"The algorithm used is closely related to the key issued as different algorithms require different key sizes (and other\\nrequirements). While some keys can be used for multiple algorithm, the protocol is designed to closely bind the key and algorithm\\ntogether as part of the issued credentials.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"why-is-host-and-content-type-the-only-headers-covered-by-the-request-mac\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#why-is-host-and-content-type-the-only-headers-covered-by-the-request-mac\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Why is Host and Content-Type the only headers covered by the request MAC?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v('It is really hard to include other headers. Headers can be changed by proxies and other intermediaries and there is no\\nwell-established way to normalize them. Many platforms change the case of header field names and values. The only\\nstraight-forward solution is to include the headers in some blob (say, base64 encoded JSON) and include that with the request,\\nan approach taken by JWT and other such formats. However, that design violates the HTTP header boundaries, repeats information,\\nand introduces other security issues because firewalls will not be aware of these \"hidden\" headers. In addition, any information\\nrepeated must be compared to the duplicated information in the header and therefore only moves the problem elsewhere.')]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"why-not-just-use-http-digest\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#why-not-just-use-http-digest\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Why not just use HTTP Digest?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"Digest requires pre-negotiation to establish a nonce. This means you can't just make a request - you must first send\\na protocol handshake to the server. This pattern has become unacceptable for most web services, especially mobile\\nwhere extra round-trip are costly.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"why-bother-with-all-this-nonce-and-timestamp-business\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#why-bother-with-all-this-nonce-and-timestamp-business\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Why bother with all this nonce and timestamp business?\")]),a(\"p\",[a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" is an attempt to find a reasonable, practical compromise between security and usability. OAuth 1.0 got timestamp\\nand nonces halfway right but failed when it came to scalability and consistent developer experience. \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" addresses\\nit by requiring the client to sync its clock, but provides it with tools to accomplish it.\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"In general, replay protection is a matter of application-specific threat model. It is less of an issue on a TLS-protected\\nsystem where the clients are implemented using best practices and are under the control of the server. Instead of dropping\\nreplay protection, \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" offers a required time window and an optional nonce verification. Together, it provides developers\\nwith the ability to decide how to enforce their security policy without impacting the client's implementation.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"what-are-app-and-dlg-in-the-authorization-header-and-normalized-mac-string\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#what-are-app-and-dlg-in-the-authorization-header-and-normalized-mac-string\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" What are \"),a(\"code\",[t._v(\"app\")]),t._v(\" and \"),a(\"code\",[t._v(\"dlg\")]),t._v(\" in the authorization header and normalized mac string?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"The original motivation for \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" was to replace the OAuth 1.0 use cases. This included both a simple client-server mode which\\nthis module is specifically designed for, and a delegated access mode which is being developed separately in\\n\"),a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/hueniverse/oz\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\"}},[t._v(\"Oz\")]),t._v(\". In addition to the \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" use cases, Oz requires another attribute: the application id \"),a(\"code\",[t._v(\"app\")]),t._v(\".\\nThis provides binding between the credentials and the application in a way that prevents an attacker from tricking an application\\nto use credentials issued to someone else. It also has an optional 'delegated-by' attribute \"),a(\"code\",[t._v(\"dlg\")]),t._v(\" which is the application id of the\\napplication the credentials were directly issued to. The goal of these two additions is to allow Oz to utilize \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" directly,\\nbut with the additional security of delegated credentials.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"what-is-the-purpose-of-the-static-strings-used-in-each-normalized-mac-input\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#what-is-the-purpose-of-the-static-strings-used-in-each-normalized-mac-input\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" What is the purpose of the static strings used in each normalized MAC input?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"When calculating a hash or MAC, a static prefix (tag) is added. The prefix is used to prevent MAC values from being\\nused or reused for a purpose other than what they were created for (i.e. prevents switching MAC values between a request,\\nresponse, and a bewit use cases). It also protects against exploits created after a potential change in how the protocol\\ncreates the normalized string. For example, if a future version would switch the order of nonce and timestamp, it\\ncan create an exploit opportunity for cases where the nonce is similar in format to a timestamp.\")]),a(\"h3\",{attrs:{id:\"does-hawk-have-anything-to-do-with-oauth\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#does-hawk-have-anything-to-do-with-oauth\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Does \"),a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" have anything to do with OAuth?\")]),a(\"p\",[t._v(\"Short answer: no.\")]),a(\"p\",[a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" was originally proposed as the OAuth MAC Token specification. However, the OAuth working group in its consistent\\nincompetence failed to produce a final, usable solution to address one of the most popular use cases of OAuth 1.0 - using it\\nto authenticate simple client-server transactions (i.e. two-legged). As you can guess, the OAuth working group is still hard\\nat work to produce more garbage.\")]),a(\"p\",[a(\"strong\",[t._v(\"Hawk\")]),t._v(\" provides a simple HTTP authentication scheme for making client-server requests. It does not address the OAuth use case\\nof delegating access to a third party. If you are looking for an OAuth alternative, check out \"),a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/hueniverse/oz\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\"}},[t._v(\"Oz\")]),t._v(\".\")]),a(\"h1\",{attrs:{id:\"implementations\"}},[a(\"a\",{staticClass:\"header-anchor\",attrs:{href:\"#implementations\",\"aria-hidden\":\"true\"}},[t._v(\"#\")]),t._v(\" Implementations\")]),a(\"ul\",[a(\"li\",[a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/logibit/logibit.hawk/\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\"}},[t._v(\"Logibit Hawk in F#/.Net\")])]),a(\"li\",[a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/tent/hawk-ruby\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\"}},[t._v(\"Tent Hawk in Ruby\")])]),a(\"li\",[a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/wealdtech/hawk\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\"}},[t._v(\"Wealdtech in Java\")])]),a(\"li\",[a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/kumar303/mohawk/\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\"}},[t._v(\"Kumar's Mohawk in Python\")])]),a(\"li\",[a(\"a\",{attrs:{href:\"https://github.com/hiyosi/hawk\",target:\"_blank\",rel:\"noopener noreferrer\